          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>November
                                                  21<hi rend="sup">st</hi>. 1847</date></p>
                              <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">The obituary on the death of <persName>Miss G.
                                                  Aguilar</persName><lb/> has doubtless reached you
                                        ere this, and I sincerely hope that<lb/> it may meet your
                                        approval and appear in the <hi rend="underline"
                                                  ><date>December</date></hi><lb/> No. of your very
                                        excellent work; in the event of which<lb/> if you will mail
                                        the copy containing it, to my address, to<lb/> use a
                                        mercantile phra<del>i</del>se I will credit you with my
                                        thanks.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">When I had the pleasure of writing you on<lb/> the
                                                  <date>8th</date>, I was mistaken as regarded the
                                        obituary notice<lb/> therein alluded to. It must have
                                        appeared in <date>April or<lb/> May, 1844</date> and not
                                                  <date>43</date> as stated; but I presume that
                                        you<lb/> had not spare copies of that no., in consequence of
                                        the length of time since its publication.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I hope that you are not inadvertently
                                        subject=<lb/>-ed to Postage, as this, and the previous
                                        letters were <hi rend="underline">franked</hi>[?] by<lb/> my
                                        friend, Honorable <persName>J. M. Woodruff</persName>,
                                        Member of Congress, from<lb/> this city.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Truly, and Respectfully,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Uriah H.
                                        Judah</persName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <placeName>143 Maiden Lane</placeName>
                              </p>
